        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-02-14 07:40:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> @Sylvain\n> It's not that I'm against having all componensts in a single repo (I support you in this manner) but I think this could be done a little bit differently.\n> \n> How about just changing approach and instead of having one giant config file for whole ONAP in robot pod have every component define it's own config and upload it to the kubernetes cluster as a config map. Then in robot you would just reference and mount those config maps and we are all done.\n> \n> What do you think?\n\nYes why not but I'm not sure it's easily feasible for robot. \n@Brian, @Daniel, would it be doable and OK for you?",
        "patchset_number": 1
